('El Espanol Restaurant', 'Spanish restaurant', 'Our El Espanol
It is widely known that the Philippines was a Spanish colony for 333 years, so it comes as no surprise that Spanish culture had a significant influence on Filipino cuisine with about 80% of Filipino dishes having Spanish roots.

A lesser known fact is that the name La Pampanga was given to our province by the Spaniards in 1571, making it the first Spanish province in Luzon. It is only appropriate, therefore, that we promote our heritage by offering authentic, traditional Spanish cuisine in the heart of Pampanga.', 'Nepo Center, Cluster II-D, Plaridel Street, Angeles, 2009 Pampanga', 15.1338095, 120.5863083, '$', '+63 917 132 8425', NULL, 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/gps-cs-s/APNQkAEInp4WMZmovIqDm1yXBRDDatu4X94aMo7_Vw7SMcBhcl4awkEtlx5FBYaTzdVz-z-GkhJzvFJVqdg9UW0S-hWUCmL8a4KBsqgb1Nf4R0BKTCXNN4KHrYFZAiA12LkGuLYSZlo=w1920-h1080-k-no', '11:30 AM - 09:00 PM', TRUE),
